It was so special to see my mom, aunt and grandma meeting my girlfriends and it was such a lovely time 🥰
Extra grateful and a special thanks for @livewhynot and @vavavictoria__ for throwing this amazing party together ❤️.

Some of my favorite moments and photos of 2022. 
It was a year that started with a big loss of someone very dear to me. 

But it was also a year with some amazing moments. 

We visited my family in the Netherlands, celebrated Stu’s birthday in Paris, celebrated my birthday with a roadtrip through Oregon, had some great (camp) trips in the summer, spent lots of time with great friends, we went rafting, hung out on the beach in Tofino, I visited a dear friend in New York and my mom, aunt and grandma made the trip to come and visit Vancouver and celebrate my bridal shower. I am very lucky to be surrounded by beautiful people, friends and family, and to have been able to get on a plane and visit some new places. My travel heart needed those trips. 
Very thankful for this year but very much looking forward to 2023! ❤️
-
Wishing you all a very love filled new year. 
-
-

Hi! It’s a new year! So let me reintroduce myself. It’s been awhile since I have done this. 
So here are 10 things you need to know about me: 
🤍I live in North Vancouver, Canada. We bought an apartment here last year. 
🤍I am from a small town in Friesland called Kollum, in the Netherlands. I try to go back and visit every year. 
🤍I am getting married to the love of my life twice this year! In June and in september. 
🤍I absolutely love the mountains but also the beaches. It’s hard to make a choice between those two 
🤍I love to read. 
🤍I manage a cafe in Deep cove, where I bake, make coffees and do all the things in between. 
🤍I’ve lived in both New Zealand and the USA for a year 
🤍I have visited over 30 countries on 4 continents 
🤍 I love coffee and wine 
🤍I dream of one day owning a little cabin in the woods on a mountain I can escape too when life gets hectic. 
-

Happy 5 year Canada anniversary to me 🇨🇦 🍁🍾
-
Today 5 years ago I moved to Canada to be with the love of my life ❤️ 
It has definitely been a challenge missing my family and my home country, finding my own friends/community and my way around and trying to get a feeling of settling down in a country where I really didn’t know anyone but Stu. 
Its been lonely, exciting, scary but overall it’s definitely been an amazing journey. I feel like it has definitely become my home and I am very fortunate to finally feel this way. I feel a sense of beloning now. 
I can’t wait to see where the future will take me here but I have to say I’m pretty damn proud of myself.

This is the beautiful Cadaques in Spain! ❤️ 🇪🇸 
It may look like a Greek Santorini from the white houses but it’s the beautiful little coastal town of Cadaques. 
-
3 things you need to know about Cadaques: 
- It has this beautiful natural park called Cape du Crues right next to it. This park has stunning beaches, cliffs and viewpoints. Definitely worth a visit! 
- The town centre of Cadaques is super cute and full of art! 
- Speaking of art, Salvador Dalì lived in Cadaques and painted a lot of his painting here and you can still visit his home with some unfinished art works in it. Make sure you book this in advance! 
Cadaques is such a gorgeous town and definitely worth a visit!! ❤️
